Appium Introduction

👉 Appium is an open-source automation tool used for testing mobile applications on Android and iOS.

🔹 Simple Definition (Interview ⭐)

👉 “Appium is a tool used to automate mobile applications (native, hybrid, and web) without modifying the app code.”

🔹 🔹 Key Features of Appium
Supports Android & iOS
Works with multiple languages (Java, Python, etc.)
No need to modify app (black-box testing)
Uses Selenium WebDriver protocol
🔹 🔹 Types of Apps Supported
Native Apps 📱
Hybrid Apps 🌐
Mobile Web Apps 🌍
🔹 🔄 How Appium Works (Flow)
Test Script (Java + Selenium API)
        ↓
   Appium Server
        ↓
 Automation Engine (UIAutomator2 / XCUITest)
        ↓
   Mobile Device / Emulator
🔹 🔧 Working Explanation (Step-by-Step)
✅ 1. Write Test Script

👉 Using Java + Selenium methods

✅ 2. Send Request to Appium Server

👉 Script sends commands (click, sendKeys)

✅ 3. Appium Server Processes

👉 Converts commands into mobile actions

✅ 4. Automation Engine Executes
Android → UIAutomator2
iOS → XCUITest
✅ 5. Device Performs Action

👉 App opens, click happens, text entered

✅ 6. Response Back to Script

👉 Pass / Fail result

